############################################# ### Generated from PreTeXt source ### ### https://pretextbook.org ### ############################################# ## DBsubject() ## DBchapter() ## DBsection() ## Level() ## KEYWORDS() ## TitleText1() ## EditionText1() ## AuthorText1() ## Section1(not reported) ## Problem1(A.7.6.44) ## Author() ## Institution() ## Language(en-US)
DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "PCCmacros.pl", "parserImplicitEquation.pl", "contextCurrency.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ $m = random(10, 90, 5); $mdecimal = $m/100; $wdecimal = random(5, 20, 0.05); Context("ImplicitEquation"); Context()->variables->are(s => 'Real'); $r = 1 - $mdecimal; $answerdecimal = Real(Round($wdecimal/$r, 2)); Context()->variables->set(s => {limits=>[$answerdecimal - 100, $answerdecimal + 100]}); $equation = ImplicitEquation("s(1 - $mdecimal) = $wdecimal"); Context("Currency")->flags->set(trimTrailingZeros => 1); $w = Currency($wdecimal); $answer = Currency($answerdecimal);
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML In retail, the "profit margin" [`m`] of an item being sold is a number that explains what percentage of the item's shelf price is profit. For example if the profit margin is 15% or 0.15, it means that 15% of the shelf price is profit for the store. If the shelf price [`s`] is what a customer pays to buy the item and the item has a wholesale price [`w`] that the store pays to obtain the item, then these numbers are related by the formula [`s(1-m)=w\text{.}`]
Suppose the profit margin is [`[$m]\%`] and the wholesale price is [`[$w]\text{.}`] Write an equation that could be used to find the shelf price. Then find the shelf price.
[@KeyboardInstructions('Write the equation here.')@]**
[_]{$equation}{15}
[@KeyboardInstructions('Write the shelf price here.')@]**
[_]{$answer}{10}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION We start with the equation [`s(1-m)=w`] and substitute in what we know. The value for [`m`] should be [`[$mdecimal]`] and the value for [`w`] should be [`[$wdecimal]\text{.}`] So we have the equation
[```\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} s(1-[$mdecimal]) \amp= [$wdecimal]\\ s([$r]) \amp= [$wdecimal] \end{aligned} ```]
Now to solve for [`s\text{,}`] divide on each side by [`[$r]\text{:}`]
[```\newcommand{\divideunder}[2]{\frac{#1}{{\highlight{{#2}}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} \divideunder{s([$r])}{[$r]} \amp= \divideunder{[$wdecimal]}{[$r]}\\ s \amp= [$answerdecimal] \end{aligned} ```]
So the shelf price is [$answer].
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
ENDDOCUMENT();
